    • isOccupiedByOpponentWorker

      public boolean isOccupiedByOpponentWorker​(Player opponentPlayer)
      Method used to tell if the cell is occupied by an opponent player's worker. It checks if this cell's worker has a different owner from the one given to the function which would be the opponent Player.
      Parameters:
      opponentPlayer - the player that needs to be compared to this cell's owner
      Returns:
      true if the player occupying this cell is different from the player given to the function

    • canALevelBeRemoved

      public boolean canALevelBeRemoved()
      Method to call to tell if a level on this cell can be removed
      Returns:
      true if a level can be removed (unoccupied cell and a level (not dome) is present), false otherwise (occupied cell / no level on the cell / occupied by a dome)

    • canALevelBeAdded

      public boolean canALevelBeAdded()
      Method that checks if a level can be added on this cell. When it is called it calls canALevelBeAdded(false), which will do the check in the standard way
      Returns:
      true if it is possible to build a block, otherwise false

    • canALevelBeAdded

      public boolean canALevelBeAdded​(boolean bIgnoreWorker)
      Method that checks if a level can be added on this cell.
      Parameters:
      bIgnoreWorker - boolean that tells the method to make the check ignoring the worker who might occupy the cell or not (the standard check returns false if the cell is occupied by a worker. Ignoring the worker would make the check return true)
      Returns:
      true if it is possible to build a block, otherwise false

    • removeLevel

      public boolean removeLevel()
      Method that removes a level on this cell if possible
      Returns:
      true if the level was removed, otherwise false

    • addLevel

      public boolean addLevel()
      Method that adds a block to the cell if possible. When it is called it calls addLevel(false), which will add a level in the standard way (only if the cell isn't occupied by a worker or has a dome)
      Returns:
      a boolean that if it is true declares that the level could be added and was in fact added, otherwise it was not possible to add it

    • addLevel

      public boolean addLevel​(boolean bIgnoreWorker)
      Method that checks if a level can be added on this cell.
      Parameters:
      bIgnoreWorker - boolean that tells the method to make the check ignoring the worker who might occupy the cell or not (the standard check returns false if the cell is occupied by a worker. Ignoring the worker would make the check return true)
      Returns:
      true if it is possible to build a block, otherwise false
